                    "text": "The most important methods are PPTP and L2TP.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "From what I know they're used by at least 4 providers here in Samara, and that's about half of the city's internet users.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I can't give you exact links that mention PPTP or L2TP but you can for example take a look at Beeline's site at internet.beeline.ru (just to see that they've got a good number of users).", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "They have networks all over Russia and use PPTP in most of the cities and L2TP in Moscow and AFAIK St.Petersburg.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "So VPN is a must have for all Russian users.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "And yes, why not use pptp-linux like NM does?", 
